com.cloudera.cdk.morphline.api
Class Record

java.lang.Object
  com.cloudera.cdk.morphline.api.Record

public final class Record
extends Object

A record is a set of named fields where each field has a list of one or more values. A value can be of any type, i.e. any Java Object. That is, a record is a ListMultimap as in Guavaâ€™s ArrayListMultimap. Note that a field can be multi-valued and that any two records need not use common field names. This flexible data model corresponds exactly to the characteristics of the Solr/Lucene data model (i.e. a record is a SolrInputDocument). A field with zero values is removed from the record - it does not exist as such.
